cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on efficient routing in wireless networks for unmanned autonomous vehicles (UAVs), which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper deals with mobile robotic networks and proposes a novel approach to improve routing efficiency, which is a core aspect of robotics. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper leverages application layer knowledge derived from mobility control algorithms to predict future trajectories of UAVs, which involves the use of AI techniques. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a new routing protocol that integrates mobility prediction to avoid unexpected route breaks and packet loss, which falls under the scope of systems and control. 
5. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper deals with mobile robotic networks, which can be considered as a type of multiagent system, where multiple agents (UAVs) interact with each other to achieve a common goal.
